@kaminznanna You said it yourself the regime in Venezuela is still in power. 

No regime change, no treaty, no trade deal, no new constitution, no diplomacy... NOTHING CHANGED on the ground except the name signing the checks in Venezuela and only an uninformed person looks at that as a win. 

Only some with with 6 bankruptcies and 35 felonies looks at this as a success.

@InternationalScot Neither Israel or America is killing tens of thousands of it's own citizens and imprisoning more just for protesting a regime change. Nor are they the linchpin of proxy terror networks that literally kill countless of innocent civilians.  Every source claiming that story are soo biased it's not even funny so i have doubts on the legitimacy on it. One, US ROE's strictly prohibit such strikes UNLESS it was unforeseen collateral, meaning, not intentional. Like carpet bombing, but this was a precision strike. Israel, maybe, i dont know their ROEs but let's say they did, I condemn it with you. We've court-martialed our own soldiers for less during OIF and OEF campaigns. 

However, these sources are getting it from Iran and they are the same sources that are trying to downplay the strikes and have many of time created false narratives or outright lied. So, questionable at best. If true, i want those held responsible. 

Even so, that doesnt negate the fact that what we are doing over there is a necessity. The iranian people would agree, Saudi Arabia would agree, Kuwait would agree, Jordan would agree, basically every other modern muslim country that isnt stuck on the "evil west" narrative.

@lemachro Can you name one example of how the US has successfully done regime change?

